The paper deals with consistency conditions for replicated data in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of graphs to represent the proximity between computing nodes, which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of a distributed algorithm, which falls under the category of Databases (cs.DB) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of georeplication, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
